I have finally gotten around to taking better photos of the latest version of my piece, Infinite Direction. It is handmade from oil-based clay called @monsterclayusa and will be cast in bronze someday, or at least until one out there wants one. If you compare it to the last version, you will see that I tilted the wings more vertically so that the inner portion of the feathers could be seen better, reinforcing them to the body and adding the stray hair on the right side. I like this version a lot better. What do you think? Do you prefer the wings to be flatter and more horizontal or how they look now, more vertical and upright?

I’ve been ask a few times how I get the clay so smooth for my sculptures. I take a cheap paint brush and use it to brush on Ronsonal lighter fluid over the clay. For the broader areas I use a wider paint brush, and for the smaller details use a small paint brush until I get the desired looked. Use sparingly and make sure to have plenty of ventilation.

Exciting News!  I am thrilled to share that I placed in the top 10 of my first figurative sculpture competition hosted by artists @andrewjosephkeith and @prokotv ! The competition lasted two weeks, and reference images were provided.

It was an incredible honor to be recognized among such talented artists. This competition pushed me to explore new techniques and express my creativity in a whole new way. I poured my heart and soul into my sculpture, and seeing it acknowledged in the top rankings is beyond words. Thank you to everyone who supported and encouraged me throughout this journey. Your belief in me means the world. Stay tuned for more sculpting adventures!

Here is the final clay version. This time for good, I think:) artists, you now how it goes. The final version will be cast in bronze and available for sale in a limited edition. Title: Human Nature
..

From the series “Lost then Found”, this beautiful bronze sculpture titled, “Human Nature” captures the essence of who we are. It reflects the challenges we face in life and how our views and choices can change during difficult times. The sculpture incorporates the symbolic element of wood, representing layers of growth. It shows how something that was once dormant within us can be transformed and flourish. The sculpture features a bouquet of blossoming flowers, symbolizing the beauty and resilience that can emerge from within us.It serves as a reminder of the transformative power we possess to overcome obstacles and grow into something vibrant and alive.
.
